A warrant of arrest has been issued by the Durban Regional Court for Indian male Mohammed Billal Sheik, 37, and Indian female Zahida Rahaman, 42. The two were convicted for burglary but absconded before they could be sentenced. On 16 April 2013, the pair broke into a business premises in the Durban North policing precinct and stole jewellery worth more than R5 million.  Anyone with information of their whereabouts can contact the investigating officer, Detective Warrant Officer Vicky Moodley on 083 923 5299 or Captain Raymond Deokaran on 083 632 2849.